From the eternal grave?

23:22.653 --> 23:27.115
Tommy, can you hear me?
Tommy, can you hear me?

23:57.145 --> 24:03.402
See me, feel me, touch me, heal me.

24:31.972 --> 24:36.143
Surrounded by his friends,
He sits so silently and

24:36.143 --> 24:41.356
Unaware of anything.
Playing poxy pinball, picks his nose

24:41.356 --> 24:45.527
He smiles, he cries,
He pokes his tongue at everything

24:45.527 --> 24:46.570
I believe in love,

24:46.570 --> 24:52.826
But how can men who've never seen light
Be enlightened?

24:53.869 --> 25:00.125
Only if he's cured
Will his spirit's future level

25:00.125 --> 25:02.211
Ever heighten.

25:03.378 --> 25:05.964
And Tommy doesn't know what day it is.

25:05.964 --> 25:12.221
He doesn't know who Jesus was,
Or what praying is.

25:13.680 --> 25:19.937
How can he be saved
From the eternal grave?

26:37.306 --> 26:43.478
You talk about your woman,
I wish you could see mine.

26:54.823 --> 27:00.454
Everytime she starts to lovin',
She brings eyesight to the blind.

27:11.215 --> 27:17.471
You know, her daddy gave her magic.
I can tell by the way she walks.

27:26.021 --> 27:31.235
Everytime she starts to shake,
The dumb begin to talk,

28:15.654 --> 28:21.493
She's got the power to heal you,
Never fear.

28:30.878 --> 28:36.508
Just one word from her lips,
And the deaf can hear.

33:15.954 --> 33:21.460
If your child ain't all he should be now,
This girl will put him right.

33:21.460 --> 33:27.716
I'll show him what he could be now,
Just give me one night!

33:31.386 --> 33:37.643
I'm the Gypsy, the Acid Queen,
Pay me before I start.

33:37.726 --> 33:43.982
I'm the Gypsy, and I'm guaranteed
To mend his aching heart.

33:55.661 --> 34:01.208
Give us a room, close the door.
Leave us for a while.

34:01.208 --> 34:07.464
Your boy won't be a boy no more;
Young, but not a child!

34:07.464 --> 34:13.719
'Cause I'm the Gypsy, the Acid Queen,
Pay me before I start.

34:13.719 --> 34:19.976
The Gypsy, and I'm guaranteed
To tear your soul apart.

34:43.000 --> 34:48.547
Gather your wits and hold on fast,
Your mind must learn to roam.

34:48.547 --> 34:54.803
Just as the Gypsy Queen must do,
You're gonna hit the road!

36:34.570 --> 36:40.117
My work is done, now look at him.
He's never been more alive.

36:40.117 --> 36:46.373
His head it shakes, his fingers clutch.
Watch his body writhe!

41:37.080 --> 41:43.337
Do you think it's alright
To leave the boy with Cousin Kevin?

41:43.754 --> 41:48.967
There's something 'bout him I
Don't really like.

41:54.890 --> 42:00.729
I think it's alright,
Yes, I think it's alright.

42:10.447 --> 42:16.703
We're on our own, cousin.
All alone, cousin.

42:16.703 --> 42:22.960
Let's think of a game to play
Now the grownups have all gone away

42:22.960 --> 42:29.216
You won't be much fun,
Being blind, deaf and dumb,

42:29.216 --> 42:35.472
