Extra, extra, pinball bonanza!
Deaf dumb and blind kid makes the big game!

53:41.763 --> 53:46.977
Saturday, the final, he faces the champ!
Extra, extra, extra!

53:46.977 --> 53:53.233
Pinball, the big time, a million in hand!
You can rule the world from a yacht in the bay!

53:53.233 --> 53:57.404
Champagne flowing, you're popular, man!
Pinball, let's play!

53:57.487 --> 54:00.407
Tommy keeps on winning,
He's a millionaire,

54:00.407 --> 54:04.578
Momma's got a brand new Cadillac.
Hurry to the show,

54:04.578 --> 54:07.706
We're nearly on the air!
Extra, extra!

54:42.324 --> 54:45.035
Ever since I was a young boy,
I've played the silver ball.

54:45.035 --> 54:48.163
From SoHo down to Brighton,
I must have played them all.

54:48.163 --> 54:51.291
But I ain't seen nothin' like him
In any amusement hall.

54:51.291 --> 54:56.505
That deaf, dumb and blind kid
Sure plays a mean pinball.

55:04.346 --> 55:07.349
He stands like a statue,
Becomes part of the machine.

55:07.349 --> 55:10.477
Feelin' all the bumpers,
Always playin' clean.

55:10.477 --> 55:14.648
He plays by intuition.
The digit counters fall.

55:14.648 --> 55:18.819
That deaf, dumb and blind kid
Sure plays a mean pinball.

55:26.118 --> 55:29.371
He's a pinball wizard,
There has to be a twist.

55:29.371 --> 55:32.499
A pinball wizard,

55:32.499 --> 55:36.670
Got such a supple wrist!

55:37.921 --> 55:39.798
How do you think he does it?

55:39.798 --> 55:40.841
I don't know!

55:40.841 --> 55:42.384
What makes him so good?

55:44.887 --> 55:48.140
Well, he ain't got no distractions,
Can't hear no buzzers and bells.

55:48.140 --> 55:51.268
Don't see lights a-flashing,
He plays by sense of smell.

55:51.268 --> 55:54.396
Always has a replay,
Never tilts at all,

55:54.396 --> 55:59.610
That deaf, dumb and blind kid
Sure plays a mean pinball.

56:07.201 --> 56:10.329
He can't beat me now,
I've always been the champ!

56:10.329 --> 56:14.499
I know it's a trick!
No freak's gonna beat my hand!

56:40.275 --> 56:43.695
He can beat my favorite table,
He can beat the best.

56:43.695 --> 56:46.823
His disciples lead him in,
And he just does the rest.

56:46.823 --> 56:49.952
He's got crazy flipper fingers,
I've never seen them fall.

56:49.952 --> 56:55.165
That deaf, dumb and blind kid
Sure plays a mean pinball.

57:10.180 --> 57:13.517
He's a pinball wizard
There has to be a twist.

57:13.517 --> 57:16.645
A pinball wizard,
Got such a supple wrist!

57:24.695 --> 57:28.115
He's a pinball wizard
His score shoots even more

57:28.115 --> 57:33.328
A pinball wizard,
The world's new pinball lord!

57:36.999 --> 57:41.170
He's scoring more!
He's scoring more

58:12.451 --> 58:18.707
thought I was the Bally table king,
But I just handed my pinball crown to him.

01:00:24.041 --> 01:00:30.297
It rains champagne!
A son was born again!

01:00:30.589 --> 01:00:36.845
A genius untamed!
A life of wealth and fame, wealth and fame!

01:00:44.770 --> 01:00:51.026
Champagne flowing down just like rain,
Caviar breakfasts every day.

01:00:52.194 --> 01:00:58.450
Merchant banks and yachts and...
Servants and cars and private sand.

01:01:00.536 --> 01:01:06.792
See me, feel me, touch me, heal me.

01:01:38.991 --> 01:01:45.247
They flock in, thousands strong.
We'll just play along.

01:01:45.581 --> 01:01:51.837
A million in reserve.
For love, a just deserve, just deserve!

01:01:59.636 --> 01:02:05.893
Birds and flowers and peacock's wings,
Sequined gowns and birds that sing!

01:02:06.727 --> 01:02:12.983
Private planes and fishing lanes.
Bigger crowds and bigger, bigger, bigger takes.

01:02:17.154 --> 01:02:22.367
But what's it all worth?

01:02:30.292 --> 01:02:36.548
What's it all worth when my son is blind?
He can't hear the music nor enjoy what I'm buying.

01:02:37.174 --> 01:02:43.430
His life is worthless, affecting mine.
I'd pay any price to drive his plight from my mind!

01:06:21.148 --> 01:06:25.527
There's a man I've found
Could bring us all joy!

01:06:25.527 --> 01:06:30.449
There's a doctor I've found can cure the boy!
A doctor I've found can cure the boy!

01:06:30.449 --> 01:06:35.329
There's a man I've found could remove his sorrow,
He lives in this town, let's see him tomorrow,

01:07:01.813 --> 01:07:08.070
He seems to be completely unreceptive.
The tests I gave him showed no sense at all.

01:07:09.446 --> 01:07:15.702
His eyes react to light; the dials detect it.
He hears but cannot answer to your call.

01:07:57.828 --> 01:08:04.084
There is no chance, no untried operation.
All hope lies with him and none with me.

01:08:05.335 --> 01:08:11.592
Imagine though the shock from isolation,
When he suddenly can hear and speak and see.

01:08:58.095 --> 01:09:02.059
His eyes can see,
His ears can hear, his lips speak.

01:09:02.059 --> 01:09:06.229
All the time the needles flick and rock.

01:09:06.229 --> 01:09:12.486
No machine can give the kind of stimulation,
Needed to remove his inner block.

01:09:21.453 --> 01:09:27.709
I often wonder what it is he's feeling.
Has he ever heard a word I've said?

01:09:29.461 --> 01:09:35.716
Look at him, now in the mirror dreaming.
What is happening in his head?

01:09:44.059 --> 01:09:50.314
What is happening in his head?
Oooooh, I wish I knew, I wish I knew.

01:10:32.149 --> 01:10:37.237
Tommy, can you see me?
Can I help to cheer you?

01:10:37.237 --> 01:10:42.451
Tommy, can you hear me?
Can you feel me near you?

01:10:42.451 --> 01:10:48.707
Oooh, Tommy, Tommy, Tommy, Tommy.

01:11:53.897 --> 01:11:58.151
You don't answer my call
With even a nod or a twitch

01:11:58.151 --> 01:12:02.322
But you gaze at your own reflection!

01:12:02.322 --> 01:12:06.493
You don't seem to see me
But I think you can see yourself.

01:12:06.493 --> 01:12:11.707
How can the mirror affect you?

01:12:14.209 --> 01:12:17.880
Can you hear me
Or do I surmise

01:12:17.880 --> 01:12:22.050
That you fear me can you feel my temper

01:12:22.050 --> 01:12:28.307
Rise, rise, rise, rise, rise,

01:12:37.482 --> 01:12:42.905
Do you hear or fear or
Do I smash the mirror?

01:13:25.030 --> 01:13:31.286
I'm free - I'm free,

01:13:36.083 --> 01:13:41.505
And freedom tastes of reality!

01:13:43.173 --> 01:13:48.595
I'm free - I'm free,

01:13:50.973 --> 01:13:55.978
And I'm waiting for you to follow me.

01:13:57.980 --> 01:14:01.316
If I told you what it takes
To reach the highest high

01:14:01.316 --> 01:14:05.487
You'd laugh and say "Nothing's that simple. "

01:14:05.487 --> 01:14:07.573
But you've been told many times before

01:14:07.573 --> 01:14:09.658
Messiahs pointed to the door

01:14:09.658 --> 01:14:14.872
And no one had the guts to leave the temple!

01:14:33.015 --> 01:14:38.854
I'm free - I'm free

01:14:40.939 --> 01:14:46.028
And I'm waiting for you to follow me.

01:15:52.678 --> 01:15:58.934
Tommy, can you hear me?
Tommy, can you hear me?

01:16:53.572 --> 01:16:59.828
Mother, Father.
Touch me, feel me.

01:17:02.331 --> 01:17:04.708
Who am I, where did I come from?

01:17:04.708 --> 01:17:08.879
Have you known me, have you seen me?

01:17:10.756 --> 01:17:15.469
You're a hero! You are famous!
You're a champion of the young!

01:17:15.469 --> 01:17:20.682
You are rich, but it's so absurd to try
To explain all the things you've done.

01:17:20.682 --> 01:17:26.939
You're a god, and you're loved;
Thousands watch you play

01:17:27.231 --> 01:17:32.778
Pinball! It's a fever!
And you're the master of the game!

01:17:32.861 --> 01:17:39.117
And now that you're whole,
You'll be champion of their very souls.

01:17:44.039 --> 01:17:48.293
Yes, I'm healed!
Delivered from silent darkness.

01:17:48.293 --> 01:17:53.507
No more locked doors
Or stifled screams.

01:17:53.507 --> 01:17:59.763
Pinball! What I see now before me

01:18:01.223 --> 01:18:06.979
Is far beyond the game,
Beyond your wildest dreams!

01:18:12.693 --> 01:18:17.823
Those who love me
Have a higher path to follow now

01:18:18.949 --> 01:18:23.537
And you, dear mother, too
Must be prepared!

01:19:17.049 --> 01:19:22.888
Extra, extra, read all about it!
Pinball Wizard in a miracle cure!

01:19:22.888 --> 01:19:27.059
Extra, extra, read all about it!
Extra, Extra!

01:19:28.727 --> 01:19:33.398
Right now, right now, story and pictures
Pinball bonanza, a mother's joy!

01:19:33.398 --> 01:19:36.527
...to show times, lessons and actors.

01:19:54.878 --> 01:19:59.466
Outside the house Mr. Simpson announced
That Sally couldn't go to the meeting.

01:19:59.466 --> 01:20:04.680
He went on cleaning his black Rolls Royce
And she ran inside weeping.

01:20:07.516 --> 01:20:12.813
She got to her room and tears splashed the picture
Of the new Messiah.

01:20:13.438 --> 01:20:18.652
She picked up a book of her father's life
And threw it on the fire!

01:20:20.946 --> 01:20:23.782
She knew from the start
Deep down in her heart

01:20:23.782 --> 01:20:26.910
That she and Tommy were worlds apart,

01:20:29.705 --> 01:20:34.209
But her mother said, "Never mind, your part...

01:20:34.209 --> 01:20:37.337
Is to be what you'll be. "

01:20:45.971 --> 01:20:51.101
The theme of the sermon was come unto me,
Love will find a way,

01:20:51.101 --> 01:20:56.315
So Sally decided to ignore her dad,
And sneak out anyway!

01:20:56.315 --> 01:21:01.528
She spent all afternoon getting ready,
Decided she'd try to touch him,

01:21:01.528 --> 01:21:06.742
Maybe he'd see that she was free
And talk to her this Sunday.

01:21:12.372 --> 01:21:14.750
She knew from the start
Deep down in her heart

01:21:14.750 --> 01:21:17.878
That she and Tommy were worlds apart,

01:21:21.757 --> 01:21:23.717
But her mother said, "Never mind, your part...

01:21:23.717 --> 01:21:25.802
Is to be what you'll be. "

01:21:39.983 --> 01:21:45.113
She arrived at six and the place was swinging
To gospel music by nine.

01:21:45.113 --> 01:21:50.327
Group after group appeared on the stage
And Sally just sat there crying.

01:21:50.327 --> 01:21:55.541
She bit her nails looking pretty as a picture
Right in the very front row

01:21:55.541 --> 01:22:00.754
And then one of the people came on stage
And shouted, "Here we go!"

